<div class="welcome">
  <%= image_tag 'logo.png', alt: 'Malmö.rb', title: 'Malmö.rb' %>
  <p class="doc">
    <%= link_to "Slack", "http://oreslack.herokuapp.com", title: "Invite yourself to our chat channel #malmorb" %> |
    <%= link_to "Mailinglist",
    "https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!forum/malmorb", title: "Our mailing list is a Google Groups list for announcements" %>
    | <a href="http://twitter.com/malmorb">Twitter</a> |
    <%= link_to "Github Organization", "https://github.com/malmorb/" %> |
    <%= link_to "Code of Conduct", "http://berlincodeofconduct.org/", title: "Our CoC is the Berlin Code of Conduct" %>
  </p><!-- .doc -->

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card who-we-are">
      <p>A group of Ruby enthusiasts from sunny Malmö, Sweden who meet about every
        month to talk about Ruby, programming, and other related topics.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card events">
      <h2>Attend a Meeting!</h2>
      <p class="next-event"><b>Upcoming:</b> March 6
        <a href="http://www.foocafe.org/malmoe/events/1767-testing-and-types">Ruby meetup</a>
        at FooCafe.</p>

      <p>Explore Ruby together - this time Oskar Wickstrom will introduce RDL, which promises "Types, type checking, and contracts for Ruby".</p>

      <p>All events are open to all skill levels &mdash; including absolute beginners &mdash; and are free of charge.</p>

      <p><strong>Past</strong>:
        Feb 6: <em><a href="http://www.foocafe.org/malmoe/events/1768-creative-coding-documentation">Creative Coding &amp; Documentation</a></em> at FooCafe.
        Jan 9: <em><a href="http://foocafe.org/malmoe/events/1662-ruby-standard-libraries">"A guided tour of Ruby's Standard Libraries, pausing to look at the weird, the strange and the useful."</a></em> at Foocafe.
        Dec 5: <em><a href="http://foocafe.org/malmoe/events/1661-regexp-rust-elexir-dry-each-t-t-presentation">Regular Expressions: How People Use Them, And How You Can Use Them,
        dry-rb for Rails teams, Why Elixir?, Build your own Ruby native extensions with Helix and Rust</a></em> at Foocafe.
        Nov 7: <em>What is new in Ruby 2.5?</em> at eCraft.</p>

      <p><strong>Future</strong>: Do you want to do a talk or some other activity? Get in touch, join that Slack and mailing list!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card using-ruby">
      <h2>Who is using Ruby?</h2>

      <% current_page.data.organizations_using_ruby.sort_by {|o| o[:name].upcase }.each do |org| %>
          <a href="<%= org['url']%>" target="_blank"><%= org['name'] %></a>
      <% end %>

    </div>
  </div>

</div><!-- .welcome -->
